{"key":"post-25813066","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>25813066</id>\n<content>Pouring boiling water over a dry block of coir isn't going to pasteurize it.&amp;nbsp; By the time the center of the block hydrates, the water will have cooled off below pasteurization temperature, which should be maintained for at least an hour.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Next time, hydrate the coir first, then heat to 160F/70C at the center of the coir, and hold that temp for an hour.&amp;nbsp; A meat thermometer is a good investment.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>25813081</next>\n<prev>25811687</prev>\n<first>25809689</first>\n<last>25813766</last>\n<when>1550186774</when>\n<utime>02/15/19 01:26 AM</utime>\n</post>"}